<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5291&amp;p=47897#p47897</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5291&amp;p=47897#p47897"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[emulating MMC5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5291&amp;p=47897#p47897"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Any gotchas, etc.?<br /></div><br /><br />Not really.  MMC5 features are greatly separated in the register layout, so you can easily add support for features one by one without much worry.<br /><br />About the only unusual obstacle you have to face right off the bat is the fact that the BG has separate CHR space from the sprites (ie:  there's 12K of CHR "swapped in" instead of the usual 8K -- the BG uses a separate 4K for tiles so it doesn't have to share with the sprites).<br /><br />Castlevania 3 <em>does</em> rely on that.<br /><br />CV3 does not use ExRAM, I'm pretty sure.  I don't even think it uses WRAM.<br /><br />CV3 does use IRQs<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Thu Jun 11, 2009 10:25 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
